TITLE: Adding a Foreign Key Constraint in SQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a foreign key constraint to an existing column using the ALTER TABLE ALTER COLUMN syntax, linking the user_id column to the users table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tursodatabase/libsql/blob/main/libsql-sqlite3/doc/libsql_extensions.md#2025-04-11_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
ALTER TABLE emails ALTER COLUMN user_id TO user_id INT REFERENCES users(id);
```

