TITLE: Changing Colors of Overlapping Polygons in SQL
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to update polygon colors based on spatial relationships. Polygons that overlap with the query polygon are colored red, while non-overlapping polygons are colored blue. The transaction is rolled back to preserve original data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tursodatabase/libsql/blob/main/libsql-sqlite3/ext/rtree/visual01.txt#2025-04-11_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
.print '<h1>Color-Change For Overlapping Elements</h1>'
BEGIN;
UPDATE geo1
   SET clr=CASE WHEN rowid IN (SELECT geo1.rowid FROM geo1, querypoly
                                WHERE geopoly_overlap(_shape,poly))
           THEN 'red' ELSE 'blue' END;
.print '<svg width="1000" height="800" style="border:1px solid black">'
SELECT geopoly_svg(_shape,
         printf('style="fill:none;stroke:%s;stroke-width:1"',geo1.clr)
       )
  FROM geo1;
SELECT geopoly_svg(poly,'style="fill:none;stroke:black;stroke-width:2"')
  FROM querypoly;
ROLLBACK;
.print '</svg>'
```

