TITLE: Creating and Populating a Temporary Table with JSON Data in SQLite
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a temporary table 't2' with a JSON TEXT column, generates a large amount of JSON data using recursive CTEs, and inserts this data into the table. It demonstrates complex JSON object creation and array manipulation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tursodatabase/libsql/blob/main/libsql-sqlite3/test/json/jsonb-q1.txt#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
CREATE TEMP TABLE t2(x JSON TEXT);
WITH RECURSIVE
  c(x) AS (VALUES(1) UNION ALL SELECT x+1 FROM c WHERE x<25000),
  array1(y) AS (
    SELECT json_group_array(
             json_object('x',x,'y',random(),'z',hex(randomblob(50)))
           )
      FROM c
  ),
  c2(n) AS (VALUES(1) UNION ALL SELECT n+1 FROM c2 WHERE n<5)
INSERT INTO t2(x)
  SELECT jsonb_object('a',n,'b',n*2,'c',y,'d',3,'e',5,'f',6) FROM array1, c2;
```

