TITLE: Detecting F2FS Atomic Commit Support in C
DESCRIPTION: Code snippet showing how SQLite determines whether a file supports F2FS atomic commits after opening a database file on Linux. It uses the F2FS_IOC_GET_FEATURES ioctl call to check for the F2FS_FEATURE_ATOMIC_WRITE flag.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tursodatabase/libsql/blob/main/libsql-sqlite3/doc/F2FS.txt#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
u32 flags = 0;
rc = ioctl(fd, F2FS_IOC_GET_FEATURES, &flags);
if( rc==0 && (flags & F2FS_FEATURE_ATOMIC_WRITE) ){
  /* File supports F2FS atomic commits */
}else{
  /* File does NOT support F2FS atomic commits */
}
```

